history.content: <md>I am CS and Math double major and took 55 instead of 70. If you would like to take 126, then 70 is a must. Based on my experience, 70 better prepares 170 because it covers more comprehensive discrete math, although this semester 55 is equal to 70 for prerequisite requirement. Probability does not help too much for 170. 55 is indeed easier than 70 though, but if I were able to choose again, I would choose 70.</md>

Hi, I am an intended cs and applied math major, and I am mainly interested in AI/ML and Quant developer field. I am planning to take cs170, 182, 188, 189, and EECS126 or Stat 140. I am unsure if I should take math 55 or CS 70. I’ve heard Math 55 is relatively easier and run better but it doesn’t cover probability part as opposed to CS70. Also, I’ve read that you need cs 70 for cs 170. Would it be ok to take Math 55 if I am going to take CS 170 for sure? Or should I just take 70 instead? Any insight on this would be highly appreciated.
history.subject: Math 55 or CS 70
